<item>
            <title>[FLINK-24469] Incorrect calcualtion of the buffer size in case of channel data skew</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-24469</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If only a couple out of 100 input channels are active then there is a huge throughput drop is observed. I suppose it happens because of the line inside of SingleInputGate#getBuffersInUseCount:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
Math.max(1, channel.getBuffersInUseCount());

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Right now, I don&apos;t think that it makes sense to have min value as 1, perhaps zero buffer in use is also ok.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
